<h3>5.2 Analytics</h3>
<p>Cloudflare Web Analytics is designed to be <b>cookieless</b>. It does not set any cookies on your device.</p>

<h3>5.3 Managing cookies</h3>
<p>You can control cookies via your browser settings and delete them at any time. Because we only use essential cookies, disabling them may prevent the application from functioning correctly (for example, you may not be able to stay signed in).</p>

<p><i>This cookie list was last reviewed in February 2025.</i></p>

<h3>6. Data storage and security</h3>

<h3>6.1 How data is protected in transit</h3>
<p>All data transmitted between your browser and our Website is encrypted using HTTPS (TLS). All data transmitted between our application server and our backend provider (Xano) is also encrypted using HTTPS. This means your data is encrypted at every step of its journey.</p>

<h3>6.2 Xano (backend data storage)</h3>
<p>Xano encrypts stored data at rest and uses a <b>Secure Data Access Procedure (SDAP)</b> governed by role-based access controls and the principle of least privilege. Xano holds the following security and compliance certifications: SOC 2, ISO 27001, ISO 27701, and GDPR. Xano's infrastructure runs on Google Cloud.</p>

<h3>6.3 Microsoft Forms (contact form)</h3>
<p>Microsoft Forms is part of Microsoft 365, which meets GDPR compliance requirements. Contact form submissions are processed and stored within Microsoft's infrastructure.</p>

<h3>6.4 Cloudflare (DNS, SSL/TLS, and analytics)</h3>
<p>Cloudflare manages our DNS and HTTPS/SSL certificates. Cloudflare Web Analytics collects aggregated, cookieless usage statistics.</p>

<h3>6.5 The application framework</h3>
<p>ZinApp is built on Microsoft's .NET Core framework, which includes built-in security features such as HTTPS enforcement, encrypted authentication cookies, anti-forgery protection, and data protection APIs.</p>

<h3>6.6 General security statement</h3>
<p>We take reasonable technical and organisational steps to protect information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure.</p>

<h3>7. Sharing data with third parties</h3>

<p>We share data only as needed to operate the Website:</p>

<ul>
    <li><b>Cloudflare</b> (DNS/SSL, security, and cookieless analytics).</li>
    <li><b>Microsoft</b> (Microsoft Forms contact form submissions).</li>
    <li><b>Xano</b> (application data storage and APIs, for registered users only).</li>
</ul>

<p>We do not share personal data with third parties for their own marketing.</p>

<h3>8. Data retention</h3>

<ul>
    <li><b>Contact form submissions:</b> kept only as long as needed to respond to your enquiry and for reasonable record-keeping.</li>
    <li><b>Analytics:</b> Cloudflare Web Analytics provides aggregated usage trends only. No personal data is retained for analytics purposes.</li>
    <li><b>Application data:</b> data created by registered users is retained for as long as the user maintains an account. Users may request deletion of their data at any time.</li>
</ul>

<h3>9. Your rights</h3>

<p>Under UK data protection law, you may have rights including:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Access to personal data we hold about you.</li>
    <li>Correction of inaccurate data.</li>
    <li>Deletion of personal data (where applicable).</li>
    <li>Restriction of or objection to processing (in certain circumstances).</li>
</ul>

<p>To exercise your rights, contact us using the details below.</p>

<h3>10. Links to other websites</h3>

<p>The Website may contain links to third-party sites. We have no control over their content or privacy practices and accept no responsibility for them.</p>

<h3>11. Changes to this policy</h3>

<p>We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>

<h3>12. Contact us</h3>

<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy & Cookies Policy or your data, please contact us using the address shown in the Website footer.</p>

<p><b>Last updated: 17th February 2026</b></p>


